<CENTER>
<H1>Getting a Copy of <STRONG><EM>Miriad</EM></STRONG></H1>
</CENTER>
<HR>
Please read the <A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/disclaimer.txt">general disclaimer</A>.
<P>
The following are available (ftp access):
<UL>
<LI><STRONG>The full <EM>Miriad</EM> distribution.</STRONG><BR>
This is available in 
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/miriad.tar.Z">compressed</A>
(11 Mbytes),
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/miriad.tar.gz">gzipped</A>
(8 Mbytes) and
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/miriad.tar">plain</A>
(22 Mbytes) tar formats.
<EM>Note:</EM> This distribution includes
the Users and Programmer Guides, the installation notes and history of changes.
<LI><strong><a href=README.html>Installation, update and system guide</a></strong>, which includes

  <ul>  
    <li><a href="README.html#installing">Instructions for installing <em>Miriad</em></a>
    <li><a href="README.html#updates">Getting regular updates</a>
    <li><a href="README.html#individual">Rebuilding individual tasks/subroutines</a>
    <li><a href="README.html#sysdep">System-dependent issues</a>
    <li><a href="README.html#special-cases">Special case tasks</a>
    <li><a href="README.html#structure">The structure of <em>Miriad</em></a>
  </ul>

<LI><STRONG>The Users Guide.</STRONG><BR>This is available in
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/userguide.ps.Z">compressed</A>
(800 kbytes) and
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/userguide.ps.gz">gzipped</A>
postscript forms, configured for A4 paper size.
US letter paper size versions
(<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/userguide_US.ps.Z">compressed </A> and
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/userguide_US.ps.gz">gzipped</A> postscript) are also available.
<LI><STRONG>The Programmers Guide.</STRONG><BR>This is available in
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/progguide.ps.Z">compressed</A> (180 kbytes) and
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/progguide.ps.gz">gzipped</A>
postscript forms, configured for A4 paper.
US letter paper size versions
(<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/progguide_US.ps.Z">compressed</A>
and
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/progguide_US.ps.gz">gzipped</A> postscript) are also available.
This manual is rather out of date.
<LI><STRONG>A <A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/changes.txt">
History of changes</A>.</STRONG><BR>This is in text form, giving changes from the ancient 
to the recent. This reflects the the current distribution.
<LI><STRONG>A directory of
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/bindir/"> 
some statically-linked tasks.</A></STRONG>
</UL>
<EM>Miriad</EM> makes use of the following libraries:
<UL>
<LI>The <A HREF="http://astro.caltech.edu/~tjp/pgplot/">PGPLOT library</A>
(essential for <EM>Miriad's</EM> plotting tasks). This is included
in the <EM>Miriad</EM> distribution.
<LI>Generally PGPLOT needs the libX11.a library. Additionally two
<EM>Miriad</EM> utilities need the Athena widgets library.
<LI>The ATNF <A HREF="http://www.atnf.csiro.au/computing/software/rpfits.html">
RPFITS library</A>, which is only used by the task ATLOD. This library
is needed to load raw ATNF data. The binaries of this (for some architectures!)
are available in the
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/bindir/">
statically-linked binaries</A> area.
<LI> The <A HREF="ftp://prep.ai.mit.edu/pub/gnu/readline/readline-4.0.tar.gz">
GNU readline library</A>, which is an optional library to give
the <EM>Miriad</EM> shell command-line editting ability.
</UL>
Some additional software, of interest to BIMA users,
is also available
<A HREF="ftp://ftp.atnf.csiro.au/pub/software/miriad/bima.tar">from
here</A> (the ATNF does not support this).
<P>
A memo on the relative performance of <EM>Miriad</EM>
on different machines is <A HREF="http://bima.astro.umd.edu/memo/memo81.ps">
available from BIMA</A>.
</TD></TR></TABLE>
</BODY>
